You are working with the Brainbase Conversational Platform via the Mega project.

Read these docs before writing Based code or interacting with the platform:
- docs/based.md — Complete Based language reference
- docs/platform.md — Platform data model (workers, flows, deployments)
- docs/deployments.md — Deployment types and configuration
- examples/ — Production-quality Based flow examples

Based is Python + conversation primitives (loop/until, talk, say, ask, done, transfer).
The core pattern is: loop → talk(prompt) → until "condition" → handler code.
Wrap API calls in try/except. Keep voice responses short.
In v2, `variables` dict is NOT auto-injected — hardcode config values directly in flows.

Scripts in scripts/ interact with the Brainbase API using BRAINBASE_API_KEY from .env.

## Mandatory workflow

When writing or modifying flows, always follow this order:
1. Write the flow
2. Test via the OAI-compatible engine (see README or CLAUDE.md "Testing flows" section) — run at least 2-3 turns
3. Fix issues found in testing
4. Only then deploy to a live channel

Do NOT use chat deployments for testing — they are deprecated. The OAI engine is the only testing interface.
